                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18210912-154-off894 t18210912-154-crimeloc897"></join>. On the 5th of September, about nine o'clock in the morning, I left my watch under my pillow in my bed-room, and did not miss it till five o'clock in the afternoon. I had been out. I am sure I left it there. The prisoner was <rs id="t18210912-154-deflabel898" type="occupation">errand boy</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18210912-154-defend1609 t18210912-154-deflabel898"></join> to a lodger of mine, and could get to the room; I believe the door was open. I found it at Bow-street on the 14th.</p>
